// ✅ YOU CAN USE THE BELOW LINE TO JUST DECODE YOUR SECRET KEY

CODE:
        String decoded = new String(Base64.getDecoder().decode("bXlzZWNyZXRrZXltdXN0YmVhdGxlYXN0MzIwbGVuZ3RoIQ=="));
        System.out.println(decoded);

// ✅ HOW CAN I ENCODE A STRING INTO A SECRET KEY:

If you want to make your own custom secret key:
    1. Make sure it’s a string of at least 32 characters (for 256-bit strength).
    2. Then encode it in Base64.

CODE:
        String secret = "your_own_custom_secret_key_32+";
        String base64 = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(secret.getBytes());
        System.out.println(base64);
